- "blooms of models" refers to different models in the database;
- "petals" refers to the versions of each model;
- "leaves" refers to the performance metrics associated with each model version.

- "blossoms" refers to models in the `models` table;
- "released version" refers to the `version_status` column in the `versions` table with a value of 'released';
- "performance record" refers to entries in the `performances` table;
- "cost exceeding the threshold of 0.5" means the `cost` column in the `performances` table has a value greater than 0.5;
- "average expenditure" refers to the average of the `cost` column for each model.

- "mature" refers to models with more than one version and more than two metric values;
- "visited more than once" refers to models with more than one access event;
- "caretaker" refers to the user who created and updated metrics associated with the model;
- "most costly" refers to the model with the highest average cost.

- 'Models in the production garden' refers to models with a status of 'production';
- 'Bloomed with an average precision value' refers to the average value of the precision metric for a model;
- 'Threshold of the first metric's average precision' refers to the average value of the metric with `metric_id = 1`.

- The kappa metric is a measure of agreement between predicted and actual values, often used in classification models;
- A kappa value greater than 0.5 indicates a good level of agreement, suggesting that the model is performing well;
- The query focuses on the latest version of each model, ensuring that the most recent performance metrics are considered.

- 'released' versions are those that have been made available for deployment or use;
- 'model type' refers to the category of the model, such as regression or classification;
- 'average cost' is the mean cost of the model across its released versions.

- 'Best' in this context refers to the model type with the lowest average RMSE, highest average KAPPA, and highest average RHO;
- RMSE (Root Mean Square Error) measures the average magnitude of the error in the predictions;
- KAPPA (Cohen's Kappa) measures the agreement between predicted and actual values, adjusted for chance;
- RHO (Pearson Correlation Coefficient) measures the linear correlation between predicted and actual values.

- "Best performance" refers to the lowest RMSE value;
- "Most accessed" refers to the highest total number of access events;
- "Highest activity" refers to the user who has accessed the most unique models.

- 'released' version status indicates the model is in production;
- 'metric_id = 1' refers to a specific custom metric used to evaluate model performance;
- The average metric value is calculated for each model and must be greater than 0.5.

- `version_count` represents the number of versions created for each model;
- `average_rmse` is the average root mean squared error of the model, indicating the model's performance;
- The models are first sorted by the number of versions in descending order and then by the average RMSE in ascending order;
- `RMSE` is a common metric used to evaluate the accuracy of a model in regression tasks.

- "Cumulative cost" refers to the total cost accumulated for each model version;
- "Cumulative RMSE" refers to the total root mean square error accumulated for each model version;
- "Version number" represents the sequence of versions for a model, ordered by the date of creation.

- Performance score is calculated as the value of Custom Metric 1 divided by the sum of the values of Custom Metric 2 and Custom Metric 3;
- The highest performance score receives rank 1;
- The average performance score is the mean of all performance scores.

- 'production' indicates that the model is actively being used in a live environment;
- 'Regression' is a type of model used to predict continuous outcomes;
- 'most recent performance metrics' refers to the latest evaluation date for each model.

- "top-performing models" refers to models with the most recent performance metrics;
- "touched by Alice Johnson" means the models have been accessed by the user with the name 'Alice Johnson';
- "shine brighter than average" means the models have a recent RMSE below the average RMSE of all top-performing models.

- The threshold for the average performance score is 0.5;
- The performance score is calculated based on the `value` column in the `metric_values` table;
- The query considers the average performance score for each model and version on a specific evaluation date.

- The most recent performance and version of each model are considered;
- Custom metric values are compared against the average value of all custom metrics;
- The cost of the most recent performance is used to rank the models.

- "architect" refers to the user who created the models;
- "most expensive project" refers to the project with the highest cumulative cost of models;
- "accumulated to the highest peak" refers to the maximum cumulative cost.
